claude-code_2-1-212_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"aa9cb5ff-3fdb-44d3-8af8-c125c27f20ad","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"SPIKE RESULT: PASS (definitive). Ran headless Claude Code v2.1.211 in an isolated temp dir with CLAUDE.md = '@AGENTS.md' and AGENTS.md holding a canary token; the model returned the canary VERBATIM with NO approval prompt -> a project-level @AGENTS.md import in CLAUDE.md expands AGENTS.md into Claude Code's context at launch. Official docs (code.claude.com/docs/en/memory) confirm and recommend exactly this pattern (@AGENTS.md + a ## Claude Code section). No symlink fallback needed. Downstream stories S2 (6642) and 5b01 build on this proven mechanism (thin CLAUDE.md = single @AGENTS.md import). Version tested: claude 2.1.211. No stray spike files left in the tree (throwaway temp dir).","timestamp":1784255638229601001}],"created_at":1784230948419240001,"creation_channel":"unknown","deps":[],"description":"# Spike: verify Claude Code loads AGENTS.md via a `@AGENTS.md` import\n\n## What\n\nDe-risk the whole migration by confirming, hands-on, that a `CLAUDE.md` whose body is a\nsingle `@AGENTS.md` line actually pulls `AGENTS.md` into Claude Code's context at launch\n(the mechanism the research identified, but whose live doc page had a fetch bug). Document\nthe observed precedence/nesting behavior. If the import does NOT work in the installed Claude\nCode version, record the fallback decision (symlink `CLAUDE.md -> AGENTS.md`, accepting its\nWindows/tool-clobber tradeoffs) so downstream stories build on a proven mechanism.\n\n## Scope\n\nA throwaway spike in a scratch dir or worktree — no durable code change. Files touched:\na temporary `AGENTS.md` + `CLAUDE.md`. Output is a written finding recorded as a comment on\nthis ticket (and, if needed, a correction to the approach in the parent epic).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Confirmed whether `@AGENTS.md` in `CLAUDE.md` loads `AGENTS.md` into context in the\n  installed Claude Code build; result recorded as a comment on this ticket with the exact\n  version tested.\n  - Proving: comment on this ticket stating PASS/FAIL + `claude --version`.\n- [ ] If FAIL, the fallback mechanism (symlink vs. content-copy-with-sync-test) is chosen and\n  noted so the AGENTS.md story uses it.\n- [ ] No stray spike files left in the repo working tree.\n  - Proving: `git status --porcelain` clean after the spike.\n\n## De-risking results — SPIKE EXECUTED (PASS, definitive)\n\nRan headless Claude Code **v2.1.211** in an isolated temp dir: `CLAUDE.md` = `@AGENTS.md`,\n`AGENTS.md` held a canary token. The model returned the canary **verbatim** and with **no\napproval prompt** → a project-level `@AGENTS.md` import expands into context. Official docs\n(`code.claude.com/docs/en/memory`) confirm and recommend exactly this: \"Claude Code reads\nCLAUDE.md, not AGENTS.md … create CLAUDE.md [that] imports [it] … add Claude-specific\ninstructions below the import\" (literal example: `@AGENTS.md` then `## Claude Code`). Import\nrecursion max depth = 4 hops; same-repo imports need no approval (only imports OUTSIDE the\nproject tree prompt once). **Decision: use the `@AGENTS.md` import — no symlink fallback needed.**\nKEY NUANCE: imports \"load at launch\" and do NOT reduce context, so AGENTS.md must itself be\nlean; the token win comes from de-dup into docs (drives S2). This spike is resolved;\nimplementation is a no-op adopt-the-proven-pattern.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653"]],"parent_id":"81e2-ad5e-bfe2-4653","parent_status_uuid":"4458bfca-3d3b-4923-a95d-43f530d06921","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"closed","tags":[],"ticket_id":"1d75-89cb-f37e-482e","ticket_type":"task","titl